The Chronicle Business Editor THE Minister of Finance and Economic Development, Professor Mthuli Ncube, and his Environment, Climate, Tourism and Hospitality counterpart, Mangaliso Ndlovu, are engaged in joint talks with tourism industry players today to address issues affecting the sector. <img class="wp-image-548810 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/05/Minister-Ndlovu.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/05/Minister-Ndlovu.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/05/Minister-Ndlovu-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Minister Ndlovu The meeting is being conducted in Harare and the agenda covers among others; concerns over the tourism stimulus package, loan guarantee facility, tourism industry tax breaks and the tourism revolving fund, according to the Zimbabwe Tourism Authority (ZTA) spokesperson, Mr Godfrey Koti. <img class="wp-image-548811 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/05/Tourism-industry-players.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/05/Tourism-industry-players.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/05/Tourism-industry-players-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Tourism industry players in attendance Also in attendance are senior Government officials that include Zimbabwe Tourism Authority acting chief executive, Mr Givemore Chidzidzi, Treasury secretary Mr George Guvamatanga and his tourism counterpart, Mr Munesu Munodawafa, Tourism Business Council president Mr Wengai Nhau and other industry representatives.   <img class="wp-image-548812 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/05/Guvamatanga.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/05/Guvamatanga.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/05/Guvamatanga-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Mr Guvamatanga More to followâ€¦.